# Pkl @fh-dashboard project-dependency lockfile + package cache (ADR 0010,
# Track B), resolved in-process from the local lib/ — a build product. The
# server/build only ever resolves the CONSUMER project, so only the first is
# written on our own paths; the lib/ one shows up when a pkl tool (the CLI,
# pkl-lsp) is pointed at that package directly in a checkout. Both are build
# products wherever they land.
modules/fh-datastar-view/src/main/resources/dashboards/PklProject.deps.json
modules/fh-datastar-view/src/main/resources/dashboards/lib/PklProject.deps.json
modules/fh-datastar-view/src/main/resources/dashboards/home/PklProject.deps.json
modules/fh-datastar-view/src/main/resources/dashboards/.pkl-cache/
# Local `sbt dashboardServe` workspace (ADR 0010): the package-form dir a dev
# run bootstraps — its own .fh/ (base.pkl, machine.json, pins.json), seeded
# entries, dated backups, and cache — the exact shape the add-on writes under
# /homeassistant, kept out of the repo. Both the repo-root dir(s) and the
# module-relative default (the forked run cwd is the module base) are build
# products; `dashboardServe` currently points DASHBOARDS_DIR at the `-server`
# variant.
dashboard-local-dev/
dashboard-local-dev-server/
modules/fh-datastar-view/dashboard-local-dev/
modules/fh-datastar-view/dashboard-local-dev-server/

